result.execSummary:
The defendant Alejandro Palacio - Juarez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License (4th Offense Within 3 Years), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Cash Bond previously posted in the amount of $300.00 has been applied.  The remaining balance of the costs in the amount of $143.00 is to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Huber Privileges and Good Time Credit granted.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
